 The Peoples Democratic Party‘s leadership has rescheduled its planned National Congress, Board of Trustees, and National Executive Council meetings, which were previously scheduled to take place between 10 a.m. and 2:00 p.m. Former Senate Presidents David Mark and Bukola Saraki, the Chairman of the BoT Sen. Walid Jibrin, and the governors of Edo, Enugu, Adamawa, and Taraba host Governor, Samuel Ortom, among others, met behind closed doors for about two hours before filing out around midday. Read also: Lagos PDP chieftain accuses AMCON of invasion, fingers APC The postponement will allow for more consultations on difficult issues, Vanguard reported. The caucus meeting will now begin at 4 p.m., the BoT meeting will begin at 7 p.m., and the NEC meeting will begin at 8:00 p.m.